I sat down with @CapitalOneCafe, as a #CapitalOnePartner, to talk about how following my passions has led me to a life greater than I could have imagined. 

I believe we all have this opportunity. Finding and living my purpose has been challenging at times but worth it for both my wellbeing and financial wellbeing. ✨
 
When was the last time you followed your intuition with no fear or doubt? 

What if following your heart could lead you to a life filled with purpose and wellbeing?✨

node.text:
Happy Summer Solstice ✨ You can feel the change in the air as we enter into the longest day of the year and yet when we embrace duality we can also note that the Southern Hemisphere is experiencing winter solstice. 
*
As such, as we emerge from our pandemic hibernation we have the opportunity to remember those who are still suffering silently or for the world to see. You have the opportunity to shine your light bodily and fiercely despite the hardships you’ve endured. You have the opportunity to BE LOVE. With every breath, every day, every hour. Choose Love. ✨
*
Daily Morning Ritual:
💗Eye Yoga
💗Breath of Fire
💗Mindful Movement
*
Sponsored by @pukkaherbsus

node.text:
Have you dreamed of teaching yoga and wellness but don’t know how to take the leap? 

Or, not sure if you have the “business skills” or “social media skills” to grow a thriving wellness practice? 

Or maybe, you don’t think you have the TIME to get certified in yoga or holistic health? 

Listen…

I’m well aware of the “broke yoga teacher” stereotype… I was there for many years. 

Not to mention all the OTHER stereotypes we see in the wellness space. 

Stereotypes that make it easy to feel unwelcome if...

You don’t look a certain way...

You don’t live a certain way...

Or if you don’t have an IG feed full of backbends, headstands, and trips to Bali...

But I’m inviting you to put all that aside and realize yoga is more than that. More importantly...

The purpose you feel is more than that. 

Really... It is. 

Our purpose is so obvious to US, we think everyone must feel the same way…

We start thinking things like,

“Why would anyone want to learn from me?” 

or 

“What if I don’t have what it takes?”

So I’m inviting you to suspend those beliefs for a moment and see the truth: 

And the truth is, if you feel called to teach yoga or wellness ... it’s not an accident. 

Why not lean in?

Why not go deeper? 

Why not listen to that divine guidance?

For me, yoga was how I healed my body and found my daily connection to Spirit, something bigger than myself… 

It was a catalyst for personal evolution, social change, community, and an amazing tool for manifestation in my own life. 

Now, 18 years later, I would never have guessed I would be one of the world’s top spiritual health and wellness educators...

An RYT-500 yoga instructor with millions people tuning in across social to be guided by me and my @getlovedup community. 

An author...

Certified in Ashtanga, Breathwork, Life Coaching, AcroYoga, and even holding NASM, IIN and plant-based nutrition certifications….

I used to be shy about sharing my accomplishments but everyday I’m grateful for these opportunities and thank God for them...

I get to love myself, love others, and love the planet every single day…as my J-O-B

I believe you deserve that too. Click the YTT link in my bio if you’re READY✨

*
I’m still elated and grateful for being surrounded by beautiful, powerful women that celebrate and nurture everyone around them. Thank you @kristenriderdaughtrey @dhaujee and @melana.joy.freelove for coming over to play🧘🏾‍♀️🧘🏾‍♀️🧘🏾‍♀️

You don’t fail until you stop trying.✨This flow is very hard so I wanted to share the parts we struggled with and even when ended up falling out because it takes a ton of practice individually and together to execute these #acroyoga flows. I also want to address “Imposter Syndrome” because people have been asking me about it a lot so I’ll share a couple of tips on stepping out of that vibration of thinking and language into something more affirming.✨

🧘🏾‍♀️Tip 1: Try not to compare yourself to others. I know this isn’t easy but once you feel yourself slipping from inspiration (in spirit) in which you might feel excited and motivated to intimidation in which you might feel sad and uninspired that’s when you know you should focus more on where you’re at and your daily growth vs watching others. Affirmation: I have a unique purpose that reveals itself to me more and more on a daily basis.💕
*
🧘🏾‍♀️Tip 2: Try to ease up on judging yourself and others. Yes, there are some people who become an overnight sensation but MOST people have put in decades and over 10k hours (read “the tipping point” for more on this concept) If you have perfectionist tendencies just know it's because you have high standards for yourself and others but try not to dehumanize yourself or others. We all make mistakes. We all fall or hurt someone unintentionally at times. This is part of the human experience. Affirmation: I am not perfect and I don’t expect anyone else to be.💕
*
🧘🏾‍♀️You don’t have to “fake it til you make it” Be consistent in your practice of moving toward your desired goal daily and enjoy the journey. Celebrate your small wins and even your failures because that’s actually when you learn the most. Affirmation: I am worthy of all the best things life has to offer and I receive blessings daily .💕
*
Tag someone who needs to hear this. Winner from last sisterhood flow will be tagged in my stories today and we’ll be doing another giveaway on this post so whoever you tag might have a chance  to win. (tag as many people as you’d like) Prize announced in stories. Happy Saturday💃🏾
*
Thank you @kristenriderdaughtrey for trusting me💕

My Go-To Dessert:

Koya’s High Protein Brownie Bliss Balls 
 
💗2 Cups of raw walnuts
 
💗1 Cup of dates with pits (remove pits before blending)
 
💗4 T of Cocoa Bliss or Cacao powder
 
💗2 Scoops of Get Loved Up Vanilla protein powder 
 
💗2-5 drops peppermint DoTerra essential oil supplement
 
💗1 t Cinnamon
 
💗1 t of Vanilla
 
💗Pinch of Cayenne pepper powder “if you’re feeling sassy”
 *
Add walnuts to the food processor and pulse into a meal. Then add the rest of the ingredients. Mix/pulse in a high powered blender or food processor to combine. The result should be a moist, crumbly mixture.✨
 *
Then scoop out 2 rounded Tablespoon amounts and carefully form into balls — Roll in hemp seeds or cacao powder (optional). Whatever you have in your home.✨
 *
Store leftovers in a well-sealed container in the refrigerator up to 1 week or in the freezer up to 1 month.

Who in your life do you need to forgive? It can be though to have the hard conversations and speak up when fear is clutching your throat but that’s exactly what we’re being asked to do in this season. As we talk about forgiveness it’s not just about “I’m sorry” Were you heard and understood? Is there space for more clarity?✨
*
You will know those who are down for you if they care about your feelings and give you space to share when you ask...but you have to ask. You have to speak up and stand your ground.✨
*
@brialleringer takes us through her journey of finding her self-worth, forgiveness and creating a beautiful life for herself and all of the hurdles she overcame. You don’t wanna miss this episode on the @getlovedup podcast. Make sure you leave a review + share your take-aways below. Happy Monday💕

node.text:
We are all given the same number of hours in a day, and within those hours of trying to accomplish our goals, we face distractions, responsibilities outside of ourselves, & personal obligations. 

In addition, we must also work to fill ourselves up with the necessary love + care so that we can pour out to those around us. 

It can all be a bit heavy.

Which is why we have to be willing to set aside that time for stillness.

Set limits on what we allow in our space to protect us, our energy, & our spirit.  It’s in that place of stillness where we find alignment and hold open space for the essence of who we are. ✨

Make a bold move for yourself, even if it’s for a minute, and complete this Happy Place Meditation.  Because until you begin to set aside time for you, the energies of others, the distractions and responsibilities will continue to disrupt you. 🙅🏾 

You have a job to first take care of you. 💕 

Do that and watch the rest fall into place. ✨

How often do you take time to meditate? 🙏🏾💗

node.text:
I have arrived in Paradise at @gili.lankanfushi✨ This last year was the hardest year of my life as I’m sure it has been for many others. I’ve been through some traumatic times in my life but I feel like this was the year to face all the darkest I’ve ever felt and experienced and say “I love you” I’m in tears just writing this because I’m glad I didn’t give up on life the many times I wanted to. If you’ve ever felt this way. Never give up. God is always present even in the darkness. Love is always present✨
*
For my solar return I knew I needed something special to celebrate a new decade in life and I’ve had the Maldives on my vision board for over 20 years. Some dreams have manifested quickly in my life and others take quite a bit of time.✨
*
When I saw @gili.lankanfushi online I felt something special but with these uncertain times and the many hoops I had to jump through I didn’t embrace it as real until my last plane after over 24 hours of travel hit the ground.✨
*
When I saw the turquoise blue waters that are so clear you’ll think it’s filtered I just cried as I inhaled the air and took it all in. The staff at @gili.lankanfushi have treated me like family providing everything I could ever dream of from snorkeling to bike rides, yoga, massages, all the way down to plant based vegan meals for breakfast, lunch and dinner with many ingredients sourced directly for their island garden. I am beyond grateful for this experience and every person I’ve been blessed to meet along the way. I have so much more to share but for now I’ll just say I’m grateful for every person in my virtual and physical family. I love you💕
